cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CY, cs.SI 

This paper deals with the selection of input features for complex neural predictors, which is a common technique in natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML). The paper proposes a new game theoretic approach to class-dependent rationalization, which is a novel contribution to the field of NLP and ML. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves optimization and training of models, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The proposed method involves competitive players, which can be categorized under cs.CY (Computers and Society) as it deals with the interaction between humans and machines. Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed method in sentiment classification tasks, which can be categorized under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
